#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/nate/skills/marketing-and-growth/churn-prevention/references/dunning-playbook.md
M|references|Complete guide to recovering failed payments and reducing involuntary churn.
M|references|- Failed payments cause 30-50% of all subscription churn
M|references|- Most failed payments are recoverable with the right str
M|references|- Subscription businesses lose an estimated $129 billion annually to involuntary churn
M|references|- Effective dunning recovers 50-60% of failed payments
M|references|```
M|references|Day -30 to -7: Pre-dunning (prevent failures)
M|references|Day 0:         Payment fails → Smart retry #1 + Email #1
M|references|Day 1-3:       Smart retry #2 + Email #2
M|references|Day 3-5:       Smart retry #3
M|references|Day 5-7:       Smart retry #4 + Email #3
M|references|Day 7-10:      Final retry + Email #4 (final warning)
M|references|Day 10-14:     Grace period ends → Account paused/cancelled
M|references|Day 14+:       Win-back sequence begins
M|references|```
M|references|| Timing | Action |
M|references||--------|--------|
M|references|| 30 days before expiry | Email: "Your card ending in 4242 expires next month" |
M|references|| 15 days before expiry | Email: "Update your payment method to avoid interruption" |
M|references|| 7 days before expiry | Email: "Your card expires in 7 days — update now" |
M|references|| 3 days before expiry | In-app banner: "Payment method expiring soon" |
M|references|**Email template — Card expiring:**
M|references|```
M|references|Subject: Your card ending in 4242 expires soon
M|references|Hi [Name],
M|references|The card on file for your [Product] subscription expires on [date].
M|references|Update your payment method now to avoid any interruption:
M|references|[Update Payment Method →]
M|references|This takes less than 30 seconds.
M|references|— [Product] Team
M|references|```
M|references|Major card networks offer automatic card update programs:
M|references|| Service | Network | What It Does |
M|references||---------|---------|--------------|
M|references|| Visa Account Updater (VAU) | Visa | Auto-updates stored card numbers and expiry dates |
M|references|| Mastercard Automatic Billing Updater (ABU) | Mastercard | Same for Mastercard |
M|references|| Amex Cardrefresher | American Express | Same for Amex |
M|references|**Impact:** Reduces hard declines from expired/replaced cards by 30-50%.
M|references|**How to enable:**
M|references|- **Stripe**: Automatic — enabled by default
M|references|- **Chargebee**: Enabled through gateway settings
M|references|- **Recurly**: Built-in, enabled by default
M|references|- **Braintree**: Contact processor to enable
M|references|Prompt for a second payment method:
M|references|- During signup: "Add a backup payment method" (low conversion)
M|references|- After first successful payment: "Protect your account with a backup card" (better timing)
M|references|- After a failed payment is recovered: "Add a backup to prevent future interruptions" (best timing — they felt the pain)
M|references|For annual plans or high-value subscriptions:
M|references|- Email 7 days before renewal with amount and date
M|references|- Include link to update payment method
M|references|- Show what's included in the renewal
M|references|- Required by some regulations for auto-renewals
M|references|| Code | Type | Meaning | Retry? |
M|references||------|------|---------|--------|
M|references|| `insufficient_funds` | Soft | Temporarily low balance | Yes — retry in 2-3 days |
M|references|| `card_declined` (generic) | Soft | Various temporary reasons | Yes — retry 3-4 times |
M|references|| `processing_error` | Soft | Gateway/network issue | Yes — retry within 24h |
M|references|| `expired_card` | Hard | Card is expired | No — request new card |
M|references|| `stolen_card` | Hard | Card reported stolen | No — request new card |
M|references|| `do_not_honor` | Soft/Hard | Bank refused (ambiguous) | Try once more, then ask for new card |
M|references|| `authentication_required` | Auth | SCA/3DS needed | Send customer to authenticate |
M|references|**Stripe (Smart Retries — recommended):**
M|references|- Enable "Smart Retries" in Stripe Dashboard → Billing → Settings
M|references|- Stripe's ML model picks optimal retry timing based on billions of transactions
M|references|- Typically 4-8 retry attempts over 3-4 weeks
M|references|- Recovers ~15% more than fixed-schedule retries
M|references|**Manual retry schedule (if no smart retries):**
M|references|| Retry | Timing | Best Day/Time |
M|references||-------|--------|--------------|
M|references|| 1 | Day 1 (24h after failure) | Morning, same day of week as original |
M|references|| 2 | Day 3 | Try a different time of day |
M|references|| 3 | Day 5 | After typical payday (1st, 15th) |
M|references|| 4 | Day 7 | Morning of the next business day |
M|references|| 5 (final) | Day 10 | Last attempt before grace period ends |
M|references|**Retry timing insights:**
M|references|- Retry on the same day of month the original payment succeeded
M|references|- Retry after common paydays (1st and 15th of the month)
M|references|- Avoid retrying on weekends (lower ap rates)
M|references|- Morning retries (8-10am local time) perform slightly better
M|references|**Tone:** Friendly, matter-of-fact. No alarm.
M|references|```
M|references|Subject: Action needed — your payment didn't go through
M|references|Hi [Name],
M|references|We tried to charge your [card type] ending in [last 4] for your
M|references|[Product] subscription ($[amount]), but it didn't go through.
M|references|This happens sometimes — usually a quick card update fixes it.
M|references|[Update Payment Method →]
M|references|Your access isn't affected yet. We'll retry automatically, but
M|references|updating your card is the fastest fix.
M|references|Need help? Just reply to this email.
M|references|— [Product] Team
M|references|```
M|references|**Tone:** Helpful, slightly more urgent.
M|references|```
M|references|Subject: Quick reminder — update your payment for [Product]
M|references|Hi [Name],
M|references|Just a heads-up — we still haven't been able to process your
M|references|$[amount] payment for [Product].
M|references|[Update Payment Method →]
M|references|Takes less than 30 seconds. Your [data/projects/team access]
M|references|is safe, but we'll need a valid payment method to keep your
M|references|account active.
M|references|Questions? Reply here and we'll help.
M|references|— [Product] Team
M|references|```
M|references|**Tone:** Direct, clear consequences.
M|references|```
M|references|Subject: Your [Product] account will be paused in 3 days
M|references|Hi [Name],
M|references|We've tried to process your payment several times, but your
M|references|[card type] ending in [last 4] keeps getting declined.
M|references|If we don't receive payment by [date], your account will be
M|references|paused and you'll lose access to:
M|references|• [Key feature/data they use]
M|references|• [Their projects/workspace]
M|references|• [Team access for X members]
M|references|[Update Payment Method Now →]
M|references|Your data won't be deleted — you can reactivate anytime by
M|references|updating your payment method.
M|references|— [Product] Team
M|references|```
M|references|**Tone:** Final, clear, no guilt.
M|references|```
M|references|Subject: Last chance to keep your [Product] account active
M|references|Hi [Name],
M|references|This is our last reminder. Your payment of $[amount] is past
M|references|due, and your account will be paused tomorrow ([date]).
M|references|[Update Payment Method →]
M|references|After pausing:
M|references|• Your data is saved for [90 days]
M|references|• You can reactivate anytime
M|references|• Just update your card to restore access
M|references|If you intended to cancel, no action needed — your account
M|references|will be paused automatically.
M|references|— [Product] Team
M|references|```
M|references|| Setting | Recommendation |
M|references||---------|---------------|
M|references|| Duration | 7-14 days after final retry |
M|references|| Access | Degraded (read-only) or full access |
M|references|| Visibility | In-app banner: "Payment past due — update to continue" |
M|references|| Retry | Continue background retries during grace |
M|references|| Communication | Dunning emails continue |
M|references|**Option A: Full access during grace (recommended for B2B)**
M|references|- Lower friction, customer feels respected
M|references|- Higher recovery rate (they still see value)
M|references|- Risk: some customers exploit the grace period
M|references|**Option B: Read-only access (recommended for B2C)**
M|references|- Can view but not create/edit
M|references|- Creates urgency without data loss fear
M|references|- Clear message: "Update payment to resume full access"
M|references|**Option C: Immediate lockout (not recommended)**
M|references|- Aggressive, damages relationship
M|references|- Lower recovery rate
M|references|- Only appropriate for very low-cost plans
M|references|| Timing | Action |
M|references||--------|--------|
M|references|| Grace period ends | Pause account (not delete) |
M|references|| Day 1 post-pause | "Your account has been paused" email |
M|references|| Day 7 post-pause | "Your data is still here" reminder |
M|references|| Day 30 post-pause | Win-back attempt with new offer |
M|references|| Day 60 post-pause | Final win-back |
M|references|| Day 90 post-pause | Data deletion warning (if applicable) |
M|references|**Enable Smart Retries:**
M|references|1. Dashboard → Settings → Billing → Subscriptions and emails
M|references|2. Enable "Smart Retries" under retry rules
M|references|3. Set failed payment emails in Dashboard → Settings → Emails
M|references|**Custom retry rules (if not using Smart Retries):**
M|references|```
M|references|Retry 1: 3 days after failure
M|references|Retry 2: 5 days after failure
M|references|Retry 3: 7 days after failure
M|references|Final:   Mark subscription as unpaid after last retry
M|references|```
M|references|**Webhook events to handle:**
M|references|- `invoice.payment_failed` — trigger dunning
M|references|- `invoice.paid` — cancel dunning, restore access
M|references|- `customer.subscription.updated` — status changes
M|references|- `customer.subscription.deleted` — final cancellation
M|references|**Built-in dunning:**
M|references|1. Settings → Configure Chargebee → Retry Settings
M|references|2. Configure retry attempts and intervals
M|references|3. Settings → Configure Chargebee → Email Notifications → Dunning
M|references|**Dunning options:**
M|references|- Automatic retries with configurable schedule
M|references|- Built-in dunning emails (customizable templates)
M|references|- Grace period cfg per plan
M|references|**Managed dunning:**
M|references|- Paddle handles retries and dunning automatically
M|references|- Limited customization (Paddle manages the relationship)
M|references|- Webhook: `subscription.payment_failed`, `subscription.cancelled`
M|references|- Best for hands-off approach
M|references|**Revenue Recovery:**
M|references|1. cfg → Dunning Management
M|references|2. Set retry schedule per plan
M|references|3. Configure grace period and final action (pause vs cancel)
M|references|**Advanced features:**
M|references|- Machine-learning retry optimization
M|references|- Per-plan dunning schedules
M|references|- Built-in Account Updater
M|references|Don't rely on email alone. Show payment failures in the app:
M|references|```
M|references|┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
M|references|│ ⚠ Your payment of $29 failed. Update your card to    │
M|references|│ avoid losing access. [Update Payment →]  [Dismiss]   │
M|references|└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
M|references|```
M|references|**Rules:**
M|references|- Show on every page load during dunning period
M|references|- Allow dismiss (but show again next ses)
M|references|- Direct link to payment update (fewest clicks possible)
M|references|- Don't block the product — let them continue using it
M|references|```
M|references|┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
M|references|│                                     │
M|references|│  Your account will be paused        │
M|references|│  on [date]                          │
M|references|│                                     │
M|references|│  Update your payment method to      │
M|references|│  keep access to your [X] projects   │
M|references|│  and [Y] team members.              │
M|references|│                                     │
M|references|│  [Update Payment Method]            │
M|references|│  [Remind Me Later]                  │
M|references|│                                     │
M|references|└─────────────────────────────────────┘
M|references|```
M|references|| Metric | How to Calculate | Target |
M|references||--------|-----------------|--------|
M|references|| Recovery rate | Recovered payments / Total failed | 50-60% |
M|references|| Recovery rate by decline type | Recovered / Failed per type | Soft: 70%+, Hard: 40%+ |
M|references|| Time to recovery | Days from failure to successful payment | <5 days |
M|references|| Pre-dunning prevention rate | Prevented failures / Expected failures | 20-30% |
M|references|| Dunning email open rate | Opens / Sent per email | 60%+ |
M|references|| Dunning email click rate | Clicks / Opens per email | 30%+ |
M|references|| Revenue recovered (monthly) | Sum of recovered payment amounts | Track trend |
M|references|| Revenue lost to involuntary churn | Sum of failed + unrecovered amounts | Track trend |
M|references|**By company stage:**
M|references|| Stage | Typical Involuntary Churn | Target After Optimization |
M|references||-------|--------------------------|--------------------------|
M|references|| Early (< $1M ARR) | 3-5% of MRR/month | 1-2% |
M|references|| Growth ($1-10M ARR) | 2-4% of MRR/month | 0.5-1.5% |
M|references|| Scale ($10M+ ARR) | 1-3% of MRR/month | 0.3-0.8% |
M|references|```
